## Audience

The owner is a **designer with basic code skills**. Unless they ask for depth: keep chat replies **terse**, in **plain layman’s prose**, and lead with what happened / what to do next.

## Drivers

- **This migration:** quality is the paramount driver. Prefer a smaller, correct, behavior-identical slice over a fast, messy one. Stop if your own contribution looks low-quality.
- **Behavior lock:** typing feel must match pre-slice harness results. Prefer bit-identical helper outputs for the same `(text, pos)` inputs.
- **Patterns:** before inventing editor behavior, check how similar editors do it (CodeMirror, Qt `TextEdit`, Mac/Linux text fields) and prefer proven methodology.
- **Whole project:** document integrity is the absolute paramount driver — the owner’s prose must survive as plain Markdown on disk. That outranks migration speed and harness cosmetics. See [docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) § Document integrity, [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md), [docs/integrity-audit.md](docs/integrity-audit.md).

## Priority (non-negotiable)

1. Do the **next unchecked** handoff item only (Phase 0 → A1 → A2 → A3). Do not start Phase B/C until A3 is green.
2. Phase A scope: pure string math + undo in C++. **Do not** move visual/wrap (`positionToRectangle`, `goalX`, `visualLine*`) or rewrite `handleMacArrow` / key dispatch in Phase 0–A3.
3. Do **not** grow `build-keywriter.sh` with new behavior. Edits land in the fork (`edit_helper.*`, thin QML wrappers).
4. Do **not** replace Qt `TextEdit` or invent a new buffer format.
5. One migration slice per session (or one deploy cycle). Stop after ~20 minutes without sign-off for that slice; report and ask.

## Session shape

1. Read the handoff checklist; pick the next unchecked slice only.
2. Implement that slice only.
3. Verify on device for that slice (below). Check off the handoff item; update [TODO.md](TODO.md) / [docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md](docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md) as the handoff says.
4. Do not start the next slice in the same session unless the user asks.

## Verify (mandatory for the slice you shipped)

Deploy success ≠ tested.

- Writerdeck rebuild: push fork if needed → `git push` (this repo) → wait for CI → `bash scripts/fetch-keywriter-dist.sh` → `bash scripts/deploy-keywriter.sh -b` (never local `docker build` for Writerdeck).
- Relaunch Writerdeck; `journalctl -u writerdeck -n 30` — fail on QML parse errors or instant `editor process exited`.
- `bash scripts/test-edit-session.sh`
- Harness (never parallel with edit-session): Phase 0/A1 → `-t critical --fast` must stay **38/38/0**; Phase A2 → also `-t undo --fast` (**5/5/0**); Phase A3 → full `--fast` (**110/110/0**). Update [docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md](docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md) after full runs (include fork SHA + Patch LOC).
- At most one Writerdeck binary deploy per session unless the binary fails to launch.
- Do not `pkill -f /home/root/Writerdeck` (matches Writerdeck-server).

## Constraints (carry-over)

No jailbreak / Toltec; preserve OTA. Static Go for server: `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm GOARM=7`. Markdown on disk. Secrets: `secrets/remarkable.local.env` via `scripts/_env.sh`. Docs: terse Gruber prose; standing docs only (how → architecture, why → decisions, gotchas → lessons). Executable scripts: ASCII + LF.

